  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 36bccf2d2c1763242ba11eb36cdffde2, type: 3}
  m_Name: ElwoodAnnexLogProfile
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  pages:
  - text: '2097-05-23


      05:42


      Unfortunately, it happened. War has broken
      out. We received orders from Washington to head to Little Rock and we are departing
      today. The city was hit directly, but according to the last emergency transmissions
      before the networks collapsed, there may still be survivors, likely in underground
      structures and on the outskirts of the city. Command ordered us to take care
      of any survivors in the ruins.


      All access cards to the Elwood Research
      Annex have been secured and taken by technical personnel. Nothing will be left
      behind. Systems in sectors 7 through 10 must not fall into the wrong hands,
      even now.'
  - text: 'It is difficult to assess the full extent of the damage. The sky is still
      dark, radiation levels are high, and our reconnaissance drones lose signal
      every few kilometers.


      Moving along the old roads will be dangerous,
      but we have no alternative.


      They say this is not over yet. But if anyone
      is alive in Little Rock, we have a duty to find them.'
  actions:
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: d888a06a212da164fb073cbfedf6b1b3, type: 2}
  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 7cd7526653344eb4e969a1dc16ea20b7, type: 2}
